            <scopecontent>
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                                 <p>In 1852, several residents of Moro, Ill., established the Methodist Society Cemetery Association. The association, concerned with the cemetery&#039;s upkeep, survived until the 1970s, when the State of Illinois officially declared the cemetery a Religious Cemetery, exempting it from further care under the Cemetery Care Act.</p>
                                 <p>This collection includes photocopies of the society&#039;s 1852 constitution, a list of early burials with a map, statements of receipts and disbursements, and minutes of the association&#039;s trustees meetings, from the 1880s to the mid-twentieth century. The collection also contains correspondence between Lee Sutton, an association member, and August Cooper, the organization&#039;s president during the 1960s and 1970s. Several photocopies of documents relating to the cemetery&#039;s final legal status are also part of the collection.</p>
                                 <p>Reid Sutton of East Alton, Ill., Lee Sutton&#039;s father, donated the photocopies to the Library in 1978.</p>
                        </scopecontent>
            


